  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\">Marilda<br /><span style=\"font-size:80%;font-weight:normal\"> of Hull</span></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/File:Marilda_of_Hull_2_by_Riotarttherite.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Marilda of Hull 2 by Riotarttherite.jpg\" src=\"/images/thumb/8/89/Marilda_of_Hull_2_by_Riotarttherite.jpg/350px-Marilda_of_Hull_2_by_Riotarttherite.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"389\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/8/89/Marilda_of_Hull_2_by_Riotarttherite.jpg/525px-Marilda_of_Hull_2_by_Riotarttherite.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/8/89/Marilda_of_Hull_2_by_Riotarttherite.jpg/700px-Marilda_of_Hull_2_by_Riotarttherite.jpg 2x\" /></a><div>Marilda of Hull by © <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://riotarttherite.tumblr.com/\">Riotarttherite</a></div></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<hr /></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Alias</th><td>\nMouse<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Title</th><td>\nCaptain of <i><a href=\"/index.php/Mouse_(ship)\" title=\"Mouse (ship)\">Mouse</a></i></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Allegiance</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/House_Velaryon\" title=\"House Velaryon\">House Velaryon</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Crownlands\" title=\"Crownlands\">Crownlands</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Born</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_97_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">97&#160;AC</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><br /><a href=\"/index.php/Hull\" title=\"Hull\">Hull</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Father</th><td>\nA shipwright</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Lovers</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li>Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Laenor_Velaryon\" title=\"Laenor Velaryon\">Laenor Velaryon</a> <small>(disputed)</small><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></li><li>Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Corlys_Velaryon\" title=\"Corlys Velaryon\">Corlys Velaryon</a> <small>(rumored)</small><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Issue</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Addam_of_Hull\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Addam of Hull\">Addam of Hull</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></li><li><a href=\"/index.php/Alyn_of_Hull\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Alyn of Hull\">Alyn of Hull</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Books</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Rise_of_the_Dragon\" title=\"The Rise of the Dragon\">The Rise of the Dragon</a></i> (mentioned)</li></ul></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Marilda of Hull</b>, also called <b>Mouse</b>, was a trader and captain from <a href=\"/index.php/Hull\" title=\"Hull\">Hull</a> on <a href=\"/index.php/Driftmark\" title=\"Driftmark\">Driftmark</a>. She was the mother of Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Addam_Velaryon\" title=\"Addam Velaryon\">Addam Velaryon</a>, a <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonrider\" title=\"Dragonrider\">dragonrider</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Alyn_Velaryon\" title=\"Alyn Velaryon\">Alyn Velaryon</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_the_Tides\" title=\"Lord of the Tides\">Lord of the Tides</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Appearance_and_Character\">Appearance and Character</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Marilda_of_Hull&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Appearance and Character\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>A pretty woman, Marilda was known as Mouse because she was \"<a href=\"/index.php/Mouse\" title=\"Mouse\">small, quick, and always underfoot</a>\" as a girl.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> She was intelligent and adventurous.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Marilda_of_Hull&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Marilda_of_Hull%27s_family_by_Dragonsaria.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/b/b5/Marilda_of_Hull%27s_family_by_Dragonsaria.jpg/350px-Marilda_of_Hull%27s_family_by_Dragonsaria.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"446\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/b/b5/Marilda_of_Hull%27s_family_by_Dragonsaria.jpg/525px-Marilda_of_Hull%27s_family_by_Dragonsaria.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/b/b5/Marilda_of_Hull%27s_family_by_Dragonsaria.jpg/700px-Marilda_of_Hull%27s_family_by_Dragonsaria.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Marilda_of_Hull%27s_family_by_Dragonsaria.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Marilda with her father and two sons, by <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://i-aria.carrd.co/\">Dragonsaria</a></div></div></div>\n<p>Marilda was the daughter of a shipwright at <a href=\"/index.php/Hull\" title=\"Hull\">Hull</a>. She was frequently seen at the shipyards, often underfoot. Marilda was sixteen years old when she gave birth to <a href=\"/index.php/Addam_Velaryon\" title=\"Addam Velaryon\">Addam</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_114_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">114&#160;AC</a>, and she was barely eighteen when <a href=\"/index.php/Alyn_Velaryon\" title=\"Alyn Velaryon\">Alyn</a> was birthed in <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_115_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">115&#160;AC</a>. She refused to name the father of her sons.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>After her father's death a decade later, Marilda sold his shipyard and used the proceeds to captain a trading cog she called <i><a href=\"/index.php/Mouse_(ship)\" title=\"Mouse (ship)\">Mouse</a></i>. By <a href=\"/index.php/130_AC\" title=\"130 AC\">130&#160;AC</a> Marilda owned seven ships, which her sons served on.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>When Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Jacaerys_Velaryon\" title=\"Jacaerys Velaryon\">Jacaerys Velaryon</a> called for <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonseed\" title=\"Dragonseed\">dragonseeds</a> during the <a href=\"/index.php/Dance_of_the_Dragons\" title=\"Dance of the Dragons\">Dance of the Dragons</a>, Marilda claimed that her children, who had silver hair and <a href=\"/index.php/Purple_eyes\" title=\"Purple eyes\">purple eyes</a>, had been fathered by Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Laenor_Velaryon\" title=\"Laenor Velaryon\">Laenor Velaryon</a>, who had died in <a href=\"/index.php/120_AC\" title=\"120 AC\">120&#160;AC</a>. Grand Maester <a href=\"/index.php/Munkun\" title=\"Munkun\">Munkun</a> and Septon <a href=\"/index.php/Eustace_(Dance_of_the_Dragons)\" title=\"Eustace (Dance of the Dragons)\">Eustace</a> agree with Marilda's claim, but <a href=\"/index.php/Mushroom\" title=\"Mushroom\">Mushroom</a> wrote that Addam and Alyn had actually been fathered by Laenor's own sire, Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Corlys_Velaryon\" title=\"Corlys Velaryon\">Corlys Velaryon</a>, a frequent visitor to Driftmark's shipyards. After Addam became a <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonrider\" title=\"Dragonrider\">dragonrider</a> on <a href=\"/index.php/Seasmoke\" title=\"Seasmoke\">Seasmoke</a>, who was Laenor's own mount, Corlys and Jacaerys convinced Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenyra_Targaryen\" title=\"Rhaenyra Targaryen\">Rhaenyra Targaryen</a> to legitimize the <a href=\"/index.php/Bastard\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Bastard\">bastard</a> brothers as Velaryons.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-10\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Addam eventually died in the <a href=\"/index.php/Second_Battle_of_Tumbleton\" title=\"Second Battle of Tumbleton\">Second Battle of Tumbleton</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>After the death of Rhaenyra in the <a href=\"/index.php/Fall_of_Dragonstone\" title=\"Fall of Dragonstone\">fall of Dragonstone</a> and the pardoning of Corlys by Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Alicent_Hightower\" title=\"Alicent Hightower\">Alicent Hightower</a>, Alyn agreed to transport King <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon II Targaryen\">Aegon II Targaryen</a> from Dragonstone back to <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a>. Protected by a dozen Velaryon galleys, Marilda sailed the king to the capital aboard <i>Mouse</i>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_short.2C_sad_reign_of_aegon_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_short.2C_sad_reign_of_aegon_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>When Corlys died in King's Landing in <a href=\"/index.php/132_AC\" title=\"132 AC\">132&#160;AC</a>, Marilda and Lord Alyn sailed his body back to Driftmark aboard <i><a href=\"/index.php/Mermaid%27s_Kiss\" title=\"Mermaid&#39;s Kiss\">Mermaid's Kiss</a></i>. Corlys's remains were then buried at sea near <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonstone_(island)\" title=\"Dragonstone (island)\">Dragonstone</a> aboard <i><a href=\"/index.php/Sea_Snake\" title=\"Sea Snake\">Sea Snake</a></i>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_the_hooded_hand.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_the_hooded_hand.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Marilda constructed the <a href=\"/index.php/Mouse_House\" title=\"Mouse House\">Mouse House</a> at Hull during the <a href=\"/index.php/Lysene_Spring\" title=\"Lysene Spring\">Lysene Spring</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>When Alyn Oakenfist led a fleet of merchantmen to <a href=\"/index.php/Dorne\" title=\"Dorne\">Dorne</a> and the <a href=\"/index.php/Free_Cities\" title=\"Free Cities\">Free Cities</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/136_AC\" title=\"136 AC\">136&#160;AC</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_the_Tides\" title=\"Lord of the Tides\">Lord of the Tides</a> commanded from a galley named <i><a href=\"/index.php/Bold_Marilda\" title=\"Bold Marilda\">Bold Marilda</a></i>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Marilda_of_Hull&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.00</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.01</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.